title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester Model 67 - 22. (Very Clean and Very Nice)
postcontent:
A Winchester Model 67 - 22. I believe this gun was purchased around 1935-45 
The Model 67 had a 27 in (690 mm) barrel with a simple post front sight and a buckhorn rear sight that was drift-adjustable for windage. When it was first introduced, the rifle could chamber .22 Short, .22 Long, or .22 Long Rifle cartridges interchangeably. The rifle featured a stock made of plain uncheckered walnut  and was a takedown design; the barreled action was easily removed by turning a screw under the stock using a penny. A composition buttplate was used.
Several variants of the Model 67 were produced. Complete original gun, no changes ever made and shoots very accurately.
